shared_text:
Plato R-V School District
April 10 at 11:38 AM ·

Starting Friday night on April 10th, Plato High School will be joining schools around the country by turning on our baseball lights on Friday night at 8:20 p.m., and leaving them lit for 20 minutes, and 20 seconds to honor the class of 2020. We want all community members to be aware in the event someone is wondering why our lights are on.

At 8:20 p.m. on Friday night look toward PHS Baseball Field to see the glow of our support for our graduating class of 2020.

Please, continue to follow CDC guidance and stay safe and healthy. We miss all of our students and staff. You may drive by, but do not get out of your cars.
#platorv #classof2020 #covi̇d19 #coronavirus #homelearning #remoteteaching #mshsaa @mshsaaorg

We understand that some information got left off our registration forms for peewees. And that not all the kids got the forms sent home today. We apologize. It was our intention for them to all go out at the same time. However, please keep in mind we are all parent volunteers. Since this is the first year booster is attempting to run peewees, we are still working out all the kinks. We are going to be available Monday night from 4:30 to 6:30 in the cafeteria for anyone that feels more comfortable talking to us in person. It is not a requirement. We appreciate any other volunteers. Thank you for supporting Plato Athletics.

Kim Humphrey
Booster President

post_text: A question we get asked a lot is what does booster club do? The answer is this: We provide funds to the athletic programs. Sometimes that means buying extra equipment, or providing food for the athletes on a tournament day, and it also funds the athletic banquet at the end of each season. We also award scholarships to senior athletes at the end of the year, as well as funds to each of the athletic groups to use as they need. All the work is done by volunteers. If you would like to be part of booster club, or volunteer some of your time to help, it would be greatly appreciated!! There is a monthly meeting tonight at 6:30 in the cafeteria. Thanks!

shared_text:
Proactive Coaching
June 13, 2018 at 2:30 PM ·

Coach them all!
We will all have our share of players who are more talented than others. However, when we choose to be a coach, one of our great responsibilities is to coach everyone that is on the team, not just the select few with better abilities than others. We are in this for ALL kids. We should be fair and consistent in how we deal with all of our players. While there is very little that is "equal" in sports, one thing that should be equal is our commitment to making sure that we work to provide everyone on the team the opportunity to have a positive experience.
